    <div class="project-description">
      <h3>Ferndale Boys and Girls Club</h3>
      <p>Creative architecture and a combination of exterior finishes blend the new
      21,000 sq. ft. wood-framed building with historic Pioneer Park. The facility
      houses all Club functions including lunch and game rooms, kitchen, Teen
      Center, arts, crafts, tutoring, offices and a full gym. Challenges included
      pre-loading the site and raising the finish floor above the flood plain of
      the Nooksack River. We self-performed the civil, concrete, and carpentry work.
      Faux log siding and beams are unique features.</p>
